so we cross over to the parking place which is by the bus and Kristie takes out her sharpie and writes on jimmy's stomach, "we need six tickets *heart*" and he stands by the bus dancing around acting like a monkey or something. And then he sings to people about giving great oral for tickets.

the guitarist (tub ring's guitarist filling in for steve, righ? cause he broke a hip or something) comes out and we ask him if he can get us in cause we're all SO FUCKING COOL, he says he'll see what he can do. so he calls MSI's manager manager and BAM BEOTCH!! we were guest listed. we were on msi's guest list VIP hoes! we heard jimmy urine talking to the manager and we met tub ring/msi's guitarist. it was wonderful.

so we go up to the door and i play lead and say, "ya we're on the guest list" for who? then everyone joins in "msi" names? "name off everyone in our group" okay, go in. craziest thing in the whole fucking world.

so we get in and SMB is okay. then crossbreed comes on and even though ive never heard that band i thought their live performance was very good. msi was awesome. they opened with 'seven eleven' and ended with 'bitches'..they did tornado, golden eye, faggot, except 'i hate jimmy page' which i heard plenty of rant about.

afterwards we went to get gas and drinks, then mcdonalds, and decided to go around in a big circle to south tampa on dale mabry because were cool like that and wanted to get lost for a couple of hours :).


this has been the greatest comeback in concert history.
from being ticketless and having no hope of getting 6 tickets, to meeting a bassist, guitarist and tour director for 2 major bands and getting guest listed and not having to wait in line to get in :).

well, I have finally been raped in the ass by a trooper. metaphorically with a 155.50$ ticket for doing 69 in a 55. *lucky me, because normally i do around 80-85* but thats besides the point...

after getting away with nothing but dozens of eyeballs and evil glances from the police force, my day has come =\.

i admit 100% fault because well... iwas speeding... but theres always another side to a story so i will let you all know.


i left my house at 1:20 because usually takes me 20-25 minutes to reach the campus for a 2pm class. well, i was informed that i had to deposit a check into my dad's bank account, so scratch the extra 10 minute gap.

so, im still in good time to be at class on time for my ethics exam. im driving along powell road doin my usual 75-80 in the 55. then the light turns red just after nature coast... and then...... 18 fucking buses pull out right in front of me... im the ring leader behind these 18 yellow pieces of shit on wheels, and, me and just about everyone else behind me are getting edgy because there are 18 buses in front of us and were goin about 45 in a 55. 
we approach broad street for the left turn and ALL 18 of the buses are also turning left onto broad street..... about 5 cars behind me decide they don't want to wait any longer and off road it past the line of buses and take a right. so i think about it for a 5seconds and decide to do the same because there is a u-turn just up ahead about a 1/8 of a mile. 
this is the part where i get it rammed right up the ass. i speed up to 69 to get into the U-turn lane, take the U-turn and continue on my way for a good couple minutes...

the trooper pulled off the grass and got behind me...and nothing at first, so i thought i was clear... then about 2 1/2 minutes later the lights go on and im thinking to myself what, the hell???? why is he just NOW deciding to pull me over.....meh...



pull off to the side of the road hand over my license and registration then the trooper asks me the obvious question everybody gets, "do you know what ya did wrong?"
the first thought in my mind was, "ya, i forgot to stop off at dunkin donuts and get a cream filled one to go with those glazed eyes bud."
then i told the trooper, yes sir. i was speeding and you caught me, you saw me zip past that army of buses along with everyone else and i was the unfortunate one this time.
after he writes up the ticket in his vehicle for 10 minutes he comes back to my car and sees me looking at some computer programming work and says to me, "ahh good student still studying even before class. i like that."

then i think to myself, "ahh good trooper want another donut to go along with your 300 lb. fat ass?"

but i say, "thank you sir, i know i will be cautious from now on. it wasn't worth rushing to class because im already 3 times late than i would normally be. and the trooper says, "good, you take care then and be safe bud."

then as i creep back onto the road i think in my about flicking him off 15 times and giving him 'oinking' gestures.


well, thats my rant. now i get to pay 155.50 ticket and spend another 30 some dollars to take a course so i don't lose any points and my insurance rate doesn't go higher.
